Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve any large @Cauliflower Florets{300%g} and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the cauli roasts, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice lengthways.

Zest and cut the @Lime{1/2} into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir-fry the pepper chunks until beginning to soften and colour, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g} to coat and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the pak choi, @Coconut Milk{200%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}, stir to combine.

Meanwhile, drain the @King Prawns{150%g}.

Bring the curry to the boil and stir through the prawns. Simmer the curry until the veg is tender and the prawns are cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Stir the roasted cauli through the curry, then remove from the heat and stir in the @Soy Sauce{15%ml}. Squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Share the zesty rice between your #bowls{} and top with the Thai style prawn and veg curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!